{
  "caption_en": "Table 6. 1991–2020 climatology sampled at each station location from gridded products: annual precipitation (CHIRPS v2.0), mean/max/min temperature (ERA5-Land), reference evapotranspiration (TerraClimate), relative humidity (ERA5-Land), and PDSI (TerraClimate). IMPORTANT CAVEAT: ERA5-Land temperatures (Tmean, Tmax, Tmin) are ~9-km grid-cell climatologies, NOT direct in-situ point climatologies — the reanalysis grid does not resolve the strong topography of the inter-Andean valley and exhibits a systematic warm bias over mountainous terrain (+8.7 °C vs. INAMHI in-situ at the seven climatological stations). Stations sharing the same ERA5-Land grid cell may therefore show identical or nearly-identical temperature values; the station-to-pixel mapping is given in Table S8. These values are reported only for regional pattern characterisation and as inputs to the Mann-Kendall trend analysis (§4.1), where the systematic bias cancels in the inter-annual difference. For point-scale temperature, refer to the in-situ INAMHI records (1994–2013) and the lapse-rate-derived gradient (−8.24 °C km⁻¹; §3.3). PDSI: Palmer Drought Severity Index. RH: relative humidity (%). PET: potential evapotranspiration.",
